27/02/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian Defence Ministry announced that US Secretary of Defence Donald Rumsfeld has sent a letter to his Romanian counterpart, Teodor Atanasiu, praising Romania's contribution to the global fight against terrorism. According to the ministry, Rumsfeld also expressed thanks for Romania's role in the peacekeeping missions in Iraq and Afghanistan. 
In other news, French Foreign Minister Michel Barnier reaffirmed support for Romania's bid to become an EU member in 2007. Urging the completion of required reforms, Barnier emphasised that the integration process would not end in 2007 and that new challenges would continue to emerge. (Rompres - 26/02/05) 
